<div class="my-2">What you'll see, versus the stretched version:</div>
<ul>
<li><strong>Every section's content now sits in a centred ~1140px column</strong> — full-width backgrounds stay, but text and cards stop smearing across the whole monitor</li>
<li><strong>The hero is the brand card, scaled up</strong>: giant <code class="rounded-md bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-white/10">replyhiv</code><strong><code class="rounded-md bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-white/10">e</code></strong> wordmark (orange e), <em>"Your business, always answering."</em> in the italic serif underneath, the thin orange rule, then the mono kicker <code class="rounded-md bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-white/10">AI ASSISTANTS FOR SMALL BUSINESS — MELBOURNE</code> — exact same stack as the card, with your CTAs and intro line below. The ghosted outline "REPLYHIVE" background text is gone; the wordmark <em>is</em> the hero now.</li>
<li>Check it on your phone too — the wordmark scales down cleanly (clamps at 64px minimum).</li>
</ul>
<div class="my-2">If it looks right, merge <a href="https://github.com/kayrmac23-droid/Fieldr-site/pull/6" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">PR #6</a> and it ships to <code class="rounded-md bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-white/10">replyhive.com.au</code>. If anything feels off — wordmark too big, rule too wide, tagline size — say the word and I'll tune it.</div>
<div class="my-2"><strong>Where the rest stands</strong> (session expiry killed my Resend/Vercel logins, so the least-annoying path is now fully in your hands — no more logins for anyone):</div>
<ol>
<li>Add the <strong>4 Resend records</strong> in VIPControl from the table in my last message</li>
<li>Reply here → I'll verify all four resolve correctly from my side</li>
<li>Then click <strong>Verify DNS Records</strong> yourself on the Resend domain page (one button — resend.com/domains → replyhive.com.au)</li>
<li>And whenever convenient: drag <code class="rounded-md bg-black/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-white/10">og.jpg</code> (from earlier in the thread) into the repo root — with the hero now matching the card, your link previews and site will be perfectly consistent</li>
